The paper discusses a new framework for information hiding, which is relevant to the field of cybersecurity (cs.CR). The framework involves embedding information into digital activities, which could be related to multimedia (cs.MM) or social networks (cs.SI). The paper also mentions the potential applications of the framework in gaming, which could fall under the category of computational complexity (cs.CY) or game theory (cs.GT).
